BOULDER, Colo. (AP)--Prosecutors received nearly $80,000 Thursday to help finance the grand jury investigation into the JonBenet Ramsey slaying through March.
The grand jury, whose work is kept secret, began meeting in mid-September.
The city already has spent more than $1 million in its investigation.
